HEADWORD: Percipient
<hw>Per*cip"i*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>percipiens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>percipere</ets>. See <er>Perceive</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the
faculty of perception; perceiving; <as>as, a <ex>percipient</ex>
being</as>.</def> <au>Bentley.</au> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One who,
or that which, is percipient.</def></def2>
<rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

